
1. Go to '/usr/share/X11/xkb/symbols'
2. Paste 'us-krunn' in the directory.
3. Dont know if this is necessary but I did it anyway. Go to '/usr/share/X11/xkb/rules'
4. Paste 'us-krunn' in the directory.
5. Go to '/usr/share/X11/xkb/rules/evdev.xml'
6. Paste the following code in the file.
```xml

<layout>
      <configItem>
        <name>us-krunn</name>
        <shortDescription>kr</shortDescription>
        <description>Krunn</description>
        <languageList>
          <iso639Id>kor</iso639Id>
        </languageList>
      </configItem>
      <variantList/>
    </layout>
```

7. Go to '/usr/share/X11/xkb/rules/evdev.lst'
8. Paste the following code in the file.
```
us-krunn             us: English (Krunn)
```
